HEADWORD: Monocondyla
<hw>Mon`o*con"dy*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Mono-</er>, and <er>Condyle</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A group of vertebrates, including the birds and reptiles, or those
that have only one occipital condyle; the Sauropsida.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

